The following strains belonging to American Type Culture Collection (ATCC; LGC Standards S.r.l., Sesto San Giovanni, Milan, Italy) have been taken into account for the determination of antibacterial activity: 
 Staphylococcus aureus ATCC 6538; 
 Enterococcus faecalis VAN B V583 E; 
 Listeria monocytogenes ATCC 7644; 
 Escherichia coli ATCC 15325; 
 Pseudomonas aeruginosa ATCC 27853; 
 Salmonella tiphymurium ATCC 14028.
